documentation.value:
Defines the shape of an object.

```typescript
interface User {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  email?: string;
}
```

Creates a type alias for complex types.

```typescript
type StringOrNumber = string | number;
type User = { id: number; name: string };
type Result<T> = { data: T } | { error: string };
```

Constructs an object type whose property keys are `Keys` and values are `Type`.

```typescript
type PageInfo = Record<string, { title: string; url: string }>;
const pages: Record<'home' | 'about', number> = { home: 1, about: 2 };
```

Constructs a type with all properties of `Type` set to optional.

```typescript
interface Todo { title: string; description: string; }
function updateTodo(todo: Todo, fields: Partial<Todo>) { ... }
```

Constructs a type with all properties of `Type` set to required.

```typescript
interface Props { a?: number; b?: string; }
const obj: Required<Props> = { a: 5, b: 'hello' };
```

Constructs a type from the return type of a function type.

```typescript
function getUser() { return { id: 1, name: 'Alice' }; }
type User = ReturnType<typeof getUser>; // { id: number; name: string }
```

Obtains the type of a variable or property in a type context.

```typescript
const config = { port: 3000, host: 'localhost' };
type Config = typeof config; // { port: number; host: string }
```

Asserts that an expression should be inferred as its most specific (literal) type.

```typescript
const colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue'] as const;
// readonly ['red', 'green', 'blue']
```

Validates that a value matches a type without widening the inferred type.

```typescript
type Colors = Record<string, [number, number, number] | string>;
const palette = {
  red: [255, 0, 0],
  green: '#00ff00',
} satisfies Colors;
```

Declares a generic function with type parameter.

```typescript
function identity<T>(arg: T): T {
  return arg;
}
```

A function that narrows a type via a type predicate.

```typescript
function isString(value: unknown): value is string {
  return typeof value === 'string';
}
```

Creates a new type by transforming each property of an existing type.

```typescript
type Optional<T> = {
  [K in keyof T]?: T[K];
};
```

Build string types using template literal syntax.

```typescript
type EventName = `on${Capitalize<string>}`;
type Color = 'red' | 'blue';
type Size = 'sm' | 'lg';
type Token = `${Color}-${Size}`; // 'red-sm' | 'red-lg' | 'blue-sm' | 'blue-lg'
```

Immutable array that cannot be modified.

```typescript
const items: readonly string[] = ['a', 'b'];
const items2: ReadonlyArray<string> = ['a', 'b'];
```

Function that asserts a condition and narrows the type.

```typescript
function assertDefined<T>(val: T): asserts val is NonNullable<T> {
  if (val === undefined || val === null) {
    throw new Error('Value is not defined');
  }
}
```

