documentation.value:
Organizes code in a logical grouping.

```typescript
namespace Validation {
  export function isValid(s: string): boolean { ... }
}
```

Base class that cannot be instantiated directly.

```typescript
abstract class Shape {
  abstract area(): number;
  toString(): string { return `Area: ${this.area()}`; }
}
```

A special declaration that can be attached to class declarations, methods, accessors, properties, or parameters.

```typescript
function log(target: any, context: ClassMethodDecoratorContext) {
  return function (...args: any[]) {
    console.log(`Calling ${String(context.name)}`);
    return target.apply(this, args);
  };
}
```

Declares a resource that is automatically disposed when it goes out of scope.

```typescript
class FileHandle implements Disposable {
  [Symbol.dispose]() { this.close(); }
}
{
  using handle = new FileHandle();
  // handle disposed automatically
}
```

Create a typed React component (TSX).

```tsx
type Props = { label: string };

export function Button({ label }: Props) {
  return (
    <button className="btn">{label}</button>
  );
}
```

